{
  "description": "A long exposure night shot depicts a bridge spanning a body of water, likely a bay or sea. The bridge is illuminated with a series of orange lights along its length and on its support towers, creating a striking contrast against the dark water. The sky displays a gradient of colors, transitioning from a deep blue near the horizon to a softer, lavender hue higher up, suggesting either dawn or dusk. Silhouetted trees frame the image on both sides, adding depth and a natural border. A few faint lights from what appear to be boats or distant cityscapes can be seen on the water's surface. The overall composition emphasizes the scale of the bridge and its integration into the natural landscape.",
